  "prompt": "How do you file a complain against an online shopping website in consumer court?",
  "response": "To file a complaint against an online shopping website in consumer court, follow these steps:\n\n1. Documentation Preparation:\n- Collect all transaction-related documents\n- Keep purchase invoice/bill\n- Save communication records\n- Preserve product packaging/delivery details\n- Screenshot online conversations/complaints\n\n2. Attempt Direct Resolution\n- First contact the seller/website customer support\n- Raise complaint through official channels\n- Document all communication attempts\n\n3. File Consumer Complaint:\na) Online Filing:\n- Visit National Consumer Helpline website\n- Register complaint online\n- Upload necessary documents\n- Pay minimal filing fee\n\nb) Offline Filing:\n- Visit nearest Consumer Disputes Redressal Forum\n- Submit written complaint in prescribed format\n- Attach supporting documents\n- Pay nominal court fee\n\n4. Complaint Requirements:\n- Your complete personal details\n- Seller/website details\n- Nature of complaint\n- Compensation/relief sought\n- Supporting evidence\n\n5. Complaint Categories:\n- Defective product\n- Fraudulent transaction\n- Delivery issues\n- Refund problems\n- Service deficiency\n\n6. Follow-up:\n- Attend hearing dates\n- Provide additional evidence if required\n- Cooperate with court proceedings\n\nRemember to file complaint within prescribed time limits.",
